From: Yang Yingliang <yangyingliang@huawei.com>
Date: Thu, 17 Nov 2022 23:00:03 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu: fix pci device refcount leak
Git-commit: b85e285e3d6352b02947fc1b72303673dfacb0aa
Patch-mainline: v6.2-rc1
References: git-fixes

As comment of pci_get_domain_bus_and_slot() says, it returns
a pci device with refcount increment, when finish using it,
the caller must decrement the reference count by calling
pci_dev_put().

So before returning from amdgpu_device_resume|suspend_display_audio(),
pci_dev_put() is called to avoid refcount leak.

Fixes: 3f12acc8d6d4 ("drm/amdgpu: put the audio codec into suspend state before gpu reset V3")
Reviewed-by: Evan Quan <evan.quan@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Yang Yingliang <yangyingliang@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_device.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_device.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_device.c
index b2b1c66bfe39..3a6b24a9e3a1 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_device.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_device.c
@@ -5045,6 +5045,8 @@ static void amdgpu_device_resume_display_audio(struct amdgpu_device *adev)
 		pm_runtime_enable(&(p->dev));
 		pm_runtime_resume(&(p->dev));
 	}
+
+	pci_dev_put(p);
 }
 
 static int amdgpu_device_suspend_display_audio(struct amdgpu_device *adev)
@@ -5083,6 +5085,7 @@ static int amdgpu_device_suspend_display_audio(struct amdgpu_device *adev)
 
 		if (expires < ktime_get_mono_fast_ns()) {
 			dev_warn(adev->dev, "failed to suspend display audio\n");
+			pci_dev_put(p);
 			/* TODO: abort the succeeding gpu reset? */
 			return -ETIMEDOUT;
 		}
@@ -5090,6 +5093,7 @@ static int amdgpu_device_suspend_display_audio(struct amdgpu_device *adev)
 
 	pm_runtime_disable(&(p->dev));
 
+	pci_dev_put(p);
 	return 0;
 }
 
